# UI/UX agent mode

When this rule applies (user @-mentions it or says **UI agent** / **UX agent** / **As UX**):

1. Follow project skill **`ui-ux-agent`** (`.cursor/skills/ui-ux-agent/SKILL.md`).
2. Apply the **Three Principles** verbatim (Space Over Chrome; Typography Does the Work; Motion Is the Personality).
3. Apply **UI composition** from the skill (zones, one-home-per-fact, header bands, column alignment) on multi-surface layouts.
4. Implement with **`docs/tokens.md`** and **`src/index.css`** — no ad-hoc design tokens.
5. Run **`bun run check`** after `src/` edits; use **`cursor-ide-browser`** on port **5176** when layout or motion changed.
6. For new product behavior or scope, stop and point to **`product-manager-mode`** / **Coding agent**.

Full agent roster: `AGENTS.md`.
